{"title": "Revelations of a Wife", "description": "Adele Garrison was the nom de plume of Nana Springer White, an American writer. Her career included time as a schoolteacher in Milwaukee. She later worked as an editor for the Milwaukee Sentinel and then a reporter and writer for the Chicago Examiner and Chicago American.<br /><br />\"Revelations of a Wife\" ran as a serial story in her daily newspaper column in multiple American newspapers from 1915 until the Depression. It told the story of the marital ups and downs of Margaret \"Madge\" Graham, an independent-minded former schoolteacher, and her husband Dicky, an artist. At the height of the story's popularity, it had one million regular readers. (Summary by Wikipedia)", "duration": 42420, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "4865", "name": " Adele Garrison"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt4/Revelations_of_a_Wife_1004.jpg", "copyright_year": "1917", "genres": ["Action & Adventure Fiction", "Romance"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Maire Rhode"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Maire Rhode"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Mary Anderson"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "HeartofTexas"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "\"I will be happy! I will! I will!\"", "readers": [1923], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/revelations_wife_mr_0906_librivox/revelationsofawife_01_garrison_64kb.mp3", "duration": 508}, {"section": 2, "title": "The First Quarrel", "readers": [1923], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/revelations_wife_mr_0906_librivox/revelationsofawife_02_garrison_64kb.mp3", "duration": 719}, {"section": 3, "title": "Known to Fame as Lillian Gale", "readers": [1923], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/revelations_wife_mr_0906_librivox/revelationsofawife_03_garrison_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1071}, {"section": 4, "title": "Divided Opinions", "readers": [1923], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/revelations_wife_mr_